00:00:49.555 --> 00:00:51.805
To begin this braid, I'm
going to go ahead and pick up

00:00:51.805 --> 00:00:54.790
a piece of hair, basically
from her ear to her part.

00:00:54.790 --> 00:00:57.165
So it's a pretty
good-sized piece of hair.

00:00:57.165 --> 00:01:00.400
And we're going to
divide that in half.

00:01:00.400 --> 00:01:03.410
And then you're going to divide
those pieces in half again.

00:01:03.410 --> 00:01:06.090
And you want it to
be pretty much even.

00:01:06.090 --> 00:01:10.108
So just do your best to
get them fairly even.

00:01:13.600 --> 00:01:15.110
You now have four.

00:01:15.110 --> 00:01:17.340
You have the top, two
middles, and a bottom.

00:01:17.340 --> 00:01:19.630
We're going to take
those two middle pieces

00:01:19.630 --> 00:01:21.330
and we're going
to switch places.

00:01:21.330 --> 00:01:24.060
So you just cross them
over, one over the other.

00:01:24.060 --> 00:01:25.560
And then you're
still going to hold.

00:01:25.560 --> 00:01:27.070
So now you still have
your four pieces.

00:01:27.070 --> 00:01:29.528
And this is what I'm going to
call top and bottom, and then

00:01:29.528 --> 00:01:30.790
my two middles.

00:01:30.790 --> 00:01:34.760
At this point, you want to
bring the top into the center.

00:01:34.760 --> 00:01:37.083
So you just switch
those two, and you're

00:01:37.083 --> 00:01:40.790
going to bring your bottom
into the center, as well.

00:01:40.790 --> 00:01:42.760
This is just how you
start this braid.

00:01:42.760 --> 00:01:44.610
After this, it gets really easy.

00:01:44.610 --> 00:01:47.660
So you have, again-- you have
your top and your bottom.

00:01:47.660 --> 00:01:49.160
And you have your
two middle pieces.

00:01:49.160 --> 00:01:51.534
And at this point, you can
combine your two middle pieces

00:01:51.534 --> 00:01:52.730
into one.

00:01:52.730 --> 00:01:54.880
And you have your
top and bottom.

00:01:54.880 --> 00:01:58.190
And you want to bring that
top piece over the two

00:01:58.190 --> 00:02:01.220
middle pieces and combine
it with the bottom piece.

00:02:01.220 --> 00:02:03.320
So for right now,
it's one strand.

00:02:03.320 --> 00:02:05.200
And that is how you start.

00:02:05.200 --> 00:02:08.877
That little piece right there
is how you start the braid.

00:02:08.877 --> 00:02:11.210
Now we're going to pick up a
piece of hair from the top.

00:02:11.210 --> 00:02:12.751
This is where the
waterfall comes in.

00:02:12.751 --> 00:02:16.950
We're going to take it right
in between our two pieces

00:02:16.950 --> 00:02:18.420
and then drop it down.

00:02:18.420 --> 00:02:19.310
She'll hang onto it.

00:02:19.310 --> 00:02:22.090
So we didn't bring that
into the braid at all.

00:02:22.090 --> 00:02:24.330
It literally just
went through the hair.

00:02:24.330 --> 00:02:26.897
And we still have
our two pieces.

00:02:26.897 --> 00:02:28.730
Now you're going to
take your middles again.

00:02:28.730 --> 00:02:31.240
Split them back into two.

00:02:31.240 --> 00:02:33.810
And take this piece that
you still have combined,

00:02:33.810 --> 00:02:36.950
pop it in the middle,
and then you're

00:02:36.950 --> 00:02:39.920
going to take that top piece
again, and wrap it over,

00:02:39.920 --> 00:02:42.250
and combine it with
that bottom piece.

00:02:42.250 --> 00:02:44.850
And that becomes
your first stitch.

00:02:44.850 --> 00:02:47.460
So I'll do it again,
so you can see it.

00:02:47.460 --> 00:02:49.740
You're going to take a
piece of hair from the top,

00:02:49.740 --> 00:02:52.880
run it right down the
middle of the two,

00:02:52.880 --> 00:02:56.100
and have her hang onto it.

00:02:56.100 --> 00:03:00.690
So we still have our two outside
edge pieces, and our middles.

00:03:00.690 --> 00:03:04.530
Split the middles, take
your outside pieces,

00:03:04.530 --> 00:03:08.930
put them in the center, and
wrap those outside edges

00:03:08.930 --> 00:03:10.380
back together.

00:03:10.380 --> 00:03:12.380
And that's your next stitch.

00:03:12.380 --> 00:03:14.500
And you're just going to
continue this pattern,

00:03:14.500 --> 00:03:17.565
repeating for as
long as you like.

00:03:24.130 --> 00:03:27.130
Now, for me-- when I get to
about halfway back on her head,

00:03:27.130 --> 00:03:30.870
I'm actually just going
to take this, and just

00:03:30.870 --> 00:03:34.270
use those three pieces
and run a couple

00:03:34.270 --> 00:03:35.990
stitches of a normal braid.

00:03:35.990 --> 00:03:38.350
Only just to hold
this tight while I

00:03:38.350 --> 00:03:40.860
work with the other side.

00:03:40.860 --> 00:03:43.370
So we won't really end
up using this braid.

00:03:43.370 --> 00:03:47.070
This is purely just
to hold the hair.

00:03:47.070 --> 00:03:48.490
And you can have
her hold it, you

00:03:48.490 --> 00:03:51.310
can use an elastic,
whatever you need to.

00:03:54.250 --> 00:03:56.950
You can go ahead and
let go of those pieces.

00:03:56.950 --> 00:03:59.170
And you can see,
when she lets go,

00:03:59.170 --> 00:04:02.547
